            "videoId": "mSL9NJ8WJMM",
            "textDisplay": "I was born in Middle East and fought as a civilian during the war for 6 years, and survived a sniper trying to kill me 3 timesbut I survived by the grace of God!!\u003cbr\u003eI live in Sydney Australia 🇦🇺 now, and I remember 15 years ago I was in library returning my books 📚 when I heard a soft spoken old man approached me, and said g’day mam do you mind giving me a lift home?\u003cbr\u003eI looked at the librarian she said to me he lives up the road do you mind, and I said no of course not.!\u003cbr\u003eHe was so old could barely walk with his walking stick.\u003cbr\u003eI helped him to my car sat him down made sure he was comfortable, and put on his seat belt. \u003cbr\u003eI asked him while driving I said are you a veteran John he said yes, and so I thanked him for serving our country.\u003cbr\u003eWe arrived at his house again I helped him out of the car walked him to his front door,I looked up & saw his photos on the wall as a young soldier he was so handsome.\u003cbr\u003eI asked him ?\u003cbr\u003eI said John do you mind if I bring over my two sons after school to meet you they would love that?\u003cbr\u003eHe said sure no worries mate, and so I did my eldest son was 14 years old at the time..he was taking flying lessons becoming a pilot 👨\u200d✈️ was his dream.\u003cbr\u003eWe stayed over for an hour, and the same time his daughter arrived home from work she thanked me for helping her father.!\u003cbr\u003eThat was a day I will always remember & appreciate to have had the honour of meeting & talking with a veteran.\u003cbr\u003eIt’s been 15 years now, and my sons never forgotten the stories told from a veteran called John.!!\u003cbr\u003eA year later I was told by the librarian that John passed away.😔\u003cbr\u003eAu revoir 👋 à Dieu John \u003cbr\u003eRepose en paix 🪦 \u003cbr\u003eRest In Peace🎚\u003cbr\u003e♥️👏🇦🇺👋",
            "textOriginal": "I was born in Middle East and fought as a civilian during the war for 6 years, and survived a sniper trying to kill me 3 timesbut I survived by the grace of God!!\nI live in Sydney Australia 🇦🇺 now, and I remember 15 years ago I was in library returning my books 📚 when I heard a soft spoken old man approached me, and said g’day mam do you mind giving me a lift home?\nI looked at the librarian she said to me he lives up the road do you mind, and I said no of course not.!\nHe was so old could barely walk with his walking stick.\nI helped him to my car sat him down made sure he was comfortable, and put on his seat belt. \nI asked him while driving I said are you a veteran John he said yes, and so I thanked him for serving our country.\nWe arrived at his house again I helped him out of the car walked him to his front door,I looked up & saw his photos on the wall as a young soldier he was so handsome.\nI asked him ?\nI said John do you mind if I bring over my two sons after school to meet you they would love that?\nHe said sure no worries mate, and so I did my eldest son was 14 years old at the time..he was taking flying lessons becoming a pilot 👨\u200d✈️ was his dream.\nWe stayed over for an hour, and the same time his daughter arrived home from work she thanked me for helping her father.!\nThat was a day I will always remember & appreciate to have had the honour of meeting & talking with a veteran.\nIt’s been 15 years now, and my sons never forgotten the stories told from a veteran called John.!!\nA year later I was told by the librarian that John passed away.😔\nAu revoir 👋 à Dieu John \nRepose en paix 🪦 \nRest In Peace🎚\n♥️👏🇦🇺👋",
